About:
I am the ghostliest Puerto Rican/Roman Italian you will ever meet... I am an ENTJ on the MBTI. I'm not super fond of people unless they are intelligent and trustworthy, or AT LEAST somewhat good looking or useful in one way or another (superficial yet deep- just don't let the looks run out). What can I say? I appreciate brains and beauty; one or the other; both is ideal.  I keep a small ring of close friends, the rest are pretty much expendable; useful as pawns to an end, and I like it that way. It takes a bit of work to earn my trust and friendship, and though I am quick to make acquaintances and connections, I am just as quick to shed them if they are not productive. I like to get returns on my investments, and this includes time with people. Don't waste my time. You won't be happy with what I take in return. I can be your best friend or your worst enemy. Anything else is business as usual. 
I'm a typical NT in that I don't like to spend a lot of time in the "here-and-now". I have a very keen sense of reality, but am eager to change it. I tend not to be a very ideological or idealistic person so as to remain objective. I can be bit of a misanthrope, and I judge very quickly and harshly, so never ask me my thoughts unless you want an honest answer and are prepared to have your ideas dissected and handed back to you in pieces.  
You will probably come to the conclusion that I am either stupid, very mean, very smart, negative, funny or friendly as this is what I am often told. Charming right? I can be if need be. You probably would recognize me as in touch with humanity until I choose to let it fall apart- then my friend YOU would see what we are all truly made of in our hearts (insert evil laughter here).

***If I've offended you*** 
I'm very sorry, I assure you it wasn't my intention :x 
I always debate on whether I should actually put something meaningful here or just put something witty; but seeing as this is a website for personality types I guess I should tell you a bit about me :) 
Well, I love personality typing. In fact it was my trying to find out more about myself that I learned about the Myers-Briggs test and found out about the types. Originally I tested as an ENFP but I later realized that I was answering based on what I *wished* I was, not how I actually felt. 
So, turns out I'm an INFJ (only slightly more so than INTJ). I feel like I fit in much better with my profile now :) 
I'm pretty much textbook INFJ, but I wouldn't say I'm as warm and nurturing as most others seem, which worries me sometimes. Iï¿½m sarcastic, I like to play games of wit, and occasionally enjoy messing with people. Maybe it's because I have trouble being warm with others when I know how much they're dishonest with me, or I feel scorned by them (it's hard for me to let things go). I can be very nurturing and protective towards animals (and plants even, I view them as my little essences of pure life, because of how simple they are) but I'm also very realistic. I think itï¿½s because of my thinking/feeling borderline. 
My feelings towards humanity, at first, are with pessimism and borderline disgust. Humans are so complicated, mean, selfish. Myself included. 
But just when I wish I could write humans off as something I dislike I think of the amazing people I know, who are kind, warm, and genuinely good. Then I'm forced to see humanity as simply having a great capacity for both good and evil, if you think of things in terms or good and evil, but that's a whole other topic of my philosophy ;)

About:
I know what the caged bird feels, alas! 
When the sun is bright on the upland slopes; 
When the wind stirs soft through the springing grass, 
And the river flows like a stream of glass; 
When the first bird sings and the first bud opes, 
And the faint perfume from its chalice steals-- 
I know what the caged bird feels! 
I know why the caged bird beats his wing 
Till its blood is red on the cruel bars; 
For he must fly back to his perch and cling 
When he fain would be on the bough a-swing; 
And a pain still throbs in the old, old scars 
And they pulse again with a keener sting-- 
I know why he beats his wing! 
I know why the caged bird sings, ah me, 
When his wing is bruised and his bosom sore,-- 
When he beats his bars and he would be free; 
It is not a carol of joy or glee, 
But a prayer that he sends from his heart's deep core, 
But a plea, that upward to Heaven he flings-- 
I know why the caged bird sings!   
Paul Laurence Dunbar

About:
I am astonished, disappointed, pleased with myself. I am distressed, depressed, rapturous. I am all these things at once, and cannot add up the sum. I am incapable of determining ultimate worth or worthlessness; I have no judgment about myself and my life. There is nothing I am quite sure about. I have no definite convictions ? not about anything, really. I know only that I was born and exist, and it seems to me that I have been carried along. I exist on the foundation of something I do not know. In spite of all uncertainties, I feel a solidity underlying all existence and continuity in my mode of being.
The world into which we are born is brutal and cruel, and at the same time of divine beauty. Which element we think outweighs the other, whether meaninglessness or meaning, is a matter of temperament. If meaninglessness were absolutely preponderant, the meaningfulness of life would vanish to an increasing degree with each step in our development. But that is-or seems to me-not the case. Probably, as in all metaphysical questions, both are true: Life is-or has-meaning and meaninglessness. I cherish the anxious hope that meaning will preponderate and win the battle. ? C. G. Jung

About: As for the personality aspects of my life, I left my home town at 13, and my next town at 19, and wish I had kept in contact with friends.

Sometimes  i look at my life like a TV show, with episodes in which I did something random and different every time. 
I liked early PC gaming, then i became a bit of a socialite and stopped playing. I've spent time living on a camp site by the beach and earning a free stay working in their cafe, I play the guitar but i love both instrumental & electronic music, i learned capoeira & breakdancing from an Indian guy in exchange for being an actor for a play he'd written at a local theatre, then i set up my own weekly event at a local nightclub and ran that for a year before moving it to a better club which some of my friends had acquired, but eventually i found myself waiting tables for a few years before joining the claims department of a car insurance company. I worked there for several years and worked up to fraud department in a position they created for me. I loved it but then i was diagnosed with ME/CFS and couldn't work anymore. Slowly but surely it went from mild to severe and loads of other health problems began to fall on top of me. 
I'm still housebound but i make it a point of principle to summon every ounce of my being to take a holiday abroad every couple of years (whenever i can afford the money and have the strength). My two ambitions in life are A) to ensure I don't die before my parents, and B) find a way to make money and move to a coastal area in a country with a tropical climate (hot & humid), like maybe Costa Rica. :)
I can assure you I understand you, but I can also assure you, you don?t understand me.

Well I'm Shawnee! I am one of those people who seems to be of a mystery race, since no one really guesses it, but I can assure you I'm Native American, Swedish, Irish, and then some. I live in the United States, though the state I'm in is NOT the one I would have chosen first. Actually I think it would have been just ahead of Arkansas, Mississippi (even though my best friend lives there now), Alabama, and possibly Georgia. Actually pretty much anywhere that's humid. I've been to central Florida and I didn't enjoy it. I'm a westerner with a liberal bias all day erryday. 
I'm actually a really nice person, partially because I hate conflict and partially because I legitimately like people if they're likable, and if you want to be my friend then I'm pretty sure we can arrange that. Bare (bear?) in mind that I'm a little odd though -- I have an intense CreepyPasta/horror stuff addiction and it doesn't help alleviate my ever present nightmares. And by nightmares I mean awful night terrors that are hyper-realistic. Also keep in mind that I'm really moody -- as in I have ups, downs, lefts, and rights. It makes me really hard to be around, and I try not to let it interfere with other things, but in the end I can't really control it or how exactly I act while I'm in any given mood. 
Did I scare you off yet? No? Well then... welcome to my insanity! Enjoy your stay :D

We've got ourselves a serious situation down here   
?Look again at that dot. That's here. That's home. That's us. On it everyone you love, everyone you know, everyone you ever heard of, every human being who ever was, lived out their lives. The aggregate of our joy and suffering, thousands of confident religions, ideologies, and economic doctrines, every hunter and forager, every hero and coward, every creator and destroyer of civilization, every king and peasant, every young couple in love, every mother and father, hopeful child, inventor and explorer, every teacher of morals, every corrupt politician, every "superstar," every "supreme leader," every saint and sinner in the history of our species lived there-on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam. 
The Earth is a very small stage in a vast cosmic arena. Think of the endless cruelties visited by the inhabitants of one corner of this pixel on the scarcely distinguishable inhabitants of some other corner, how frequent their misunderstandings, how eager they are to kill one another, how fervent their hatreds. Think of the rivers of blood spilled by all those generals and emperors so that, in glory and triumph, they could become the momentary masters of a fraction of a dot. 
Our posturings, our imagined self-importance, the delusion that we have some privileged position in the Universe, are challenged by this point of pale light. Our planet is a lonely speck in the great enveloping cosmic dark. In our obscurity, in all this vastness, there is no hint that help will come from elsewhere to save us from ourselves. 
The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. There is nowhere else, at least in the near future, to which our species could migrate. Visit, yes. Settle, not yet. Like it or not, for the moment the Earth is where we make our stand. 
It has been said that astronomy is a humbling and character-building experience. There is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world. To me, it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another, and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot, the only home we've ever known.? 
- Carl Sagan, Pale Blue Dot: A Vision of the Human Future in Space

About:
I enjoy a challenge and long for the thrill of excitement and risk. I love people, viewing everyone and everything as part of an often extraordinary, interconnected whole. I see patterns and connections in everything. I am naturally inclined toward forming relationships with people and animals. Intense emotional experiences vital to a life of substance and I seek harmonious relationships with others and within myself. 
Some might say that I am a human guinea pig because I love to experiment on myself and with life. I am a risk taker and extremely bold! When I want something in life, I go for it. I am never afraid of taking the plunge, especially if there?s risk involved. I don?t shy away from speaking my mind in some way. Everything I do is carefully and critically calculated in my mind beforehand. It is almost as if, I am rehearsing a script with different endings in my head and I?ll try each one to see what works. I live life as it should be lived: with total enthusiasm and challenge what I fear most. 
I am unpredictably spontaneous, charismatic with a great deal of amusingly unconventional attributes. I do gain the favor of the more straitlaced individuals because in spite of my nonconformity, I am warm, affectionate, outgoing, fun, and genuinely like people. I enjoy telling stories, especially funny stories about my family and friends. If you want the world to know something, just tell me. Perfection is an illusion that I don?t buy into. Close enough is often all right with me, which may unnerve more precise thinking types. I become closer to perfection each day but even I know that absolute truth or absolute perfection does not exist because we are in a constant state of change for better or for worse- till death do we part. 
I make a good first impression. I am mature and playful, these two sides to my personality are constantly dueling it out. Part of me likes all of the finer things in life, while part of me is just like a big kid. No matter what side I choose, I am always adventurous and dramatic. I take life by the horns. I am up for fun of all kinds, and it?s hard for me to say no to a good time. I tend to go until I drop. I am outgoing and engaging, with both strangers and friends. I truly enjoy being with people and bring energy into any situation. Enthusiastic and fun, I am the first to say, ?let?s go?! 
My attention span can be short often being easily intrigued and distracted by new friends and acquaintances, forgetting about the older ones for long stretches at a time. Everyone doesn?t have to believe that I am wonderful and fascinating person. Humility? I don?t have much to be humble about! And I might as well promote myself, because no one else will. I believe that I am a pretty special person and I let everyone know about it. As long as it is true, I will let my colors shine. I am learning not to pretend to be confident within areas that I am insecure. That is a death trap. Be proud about being who you are, sure it?s alright to fake it till you make it, but be honest with yourself when things don?t work out. 
I am conscientiousness; generally good at balancing work and play, when I need to buckle down, I can usually get tasks done. But I?ve been known to goof off when I know I can get away with it. Overall my life is relatively smooth, I remain cool and collected, but sometimes I do panic; there are a few rides on the emotional roller coaster that I would like to eliminate. My self-interest overrules and others come later when I am not able to function with my A game. To Be True to Thy Own Self is the most important task I intend to successfully master. I want to know exactly who I am and exactly who God is. How can we have a relationship if we don?t even know each other. This is a mind blowing mystery to me. There are far too many riddles to solve and not enough clues. Each time I think I figure it out, I am quickly starting back from Go again with no $200 dollars. I want out. I want to escape this trap I am caught in.

I do try to express my feelings, mostly to my mom, as she is quite sensitive herself, but I feel like I can't describe the range of emotions and thoughts that keep confusing me. About:
I was born on the 4th of July, four years before the century, the fourth child of eight: four boys and four girls. I was named Elizabeth so that my parents could call me Ellie. See, we have a tradition in our family to name the kids one thing and call them by another name that has to end with an ï¿½eeï¿½ sound. Before me was William (Billy), Ruth (Ruthie), and Gennifer (Gennie). After me came Edmond (Eddie), Jonathan (Jonny), Grace (Gracie), and James (Jimmy). We also have a cat, Kitty, who came when Gracie was a baby. 
When I was a baby, I was either very, very happy, or very, very un-happy. Rarely was I calm or just content, except in my baby swing. This character trait has continued to this day. Iï¿½m either hyper, happy, and bubbly, or Iï¿½m depressed, moody, and angry. (Or, Iï¿½m in a zone, and if Iï¿½m in a zone, God help the person who interrupts me. Fair warning, donï¿½t interrupt me on the piano.) Rarely am I someone in between happy and sad. Does that make me bi-polar? Iï¿½ll have to look that up. Iï¿½ve wondered before if I have some kind of personality disorder. But in my honest opinion! I donï¿½t think some of these disorders should be called disorders, theyï¿½re just personalities. I donï¿½t like labels and boxes. I hate being told what to do or who I am. A friend asked me recently (very politely) if I might have a bit of ADD or ADHD. I donï¿½t. I think a lot of kids with ADD and ADHD really donï¿½t have a disorder problem, they have a discipline problem. Spank that kid and make him happy! Of course, thatï¿½s only true in some cases. But I digress. I donï¿½t have ADD, but I must be moving to pay attention to, say, a sermon or a seminar. I actually donï¿½t have to be moving, but I need my eyes focused on something. I usually doodle. Occasionally I take notes. Sometimes I will make a cloud of words by just scribbling whatever word the speaker is saying at that time. Sometimes Iï¿½ll trace my finger along something back and forth. I just need something, otherwise I will begin to daydream. Doodling doesnï¿½t mean I wonï¿½t daydream, but not doodling (or something of the sort) means I certainly will! 
But I donï¿½t think I have a personality disorder. I am kind of crazy though, or people tell me I am. Why am I crazy? Does everyone have these crazy thoughts and feel like saying crazy things? I bet Iï¿½m not crazy, Iï¿½m just brave. Iï¿½ll say things weï¿½re ALL thinking! Ha! So you are crazy too! I like to think that anyway. 
Iï¿½m not always crazy though, sometimes Iï¿½m just plain, straight-up awkward!

Some people say Iï¿½m brilliant and a deep thinker, some people say Iï¿½m shallow and naive. How can I be all of those things? Because Iï¿½m a responder. I react differently to different people. Itï¿½s the strangest thing. Sometimes just by the way they nod their head or phrase a question, I can feel words bubble up or simmer down. I can know two people of the same personality type and be able to communicate with only one. 
Understand, I am not being fake. Itï¿½s a natural reaction. If I tried to act the same around everyone, then I would be fake. I read this on an ENFP description once. My personality type is that of an ENFP. 
See, I told you I didnï¿½t like labels, but I lied. Iï¿½m a walking contradiction, and in a few moments Iï¿½ll tell you why that isnï¿½t true either. Also, while I act different around everyone and every group, eventually, when Iï¿½ve been friends with someone long enough, I find myself acting with them like I act with my siblings at home.     Personality wise, Iï¿½m pretty hard to read for a lot of people.  Iï¿½m very introverted, meaning that I tend to keep to myself a lot, which may lead to others thinking that I am anti social, unemotional and detached.  I am also intuitive; meaning that I tend to just learn and know things, even if thereï¿½s no apparent evidence or concrete reasoning.  I tend to not take up any leadership roles or take the initiative, unless I feel like current leadership is failing.  The reason for being so passive that I simply do not care enough to be involved; I would rather take the back seat and observe what is going on.  If there is a topic I do not understand or that I wish to learn about more, I will read about it for as long as it takes till I feel as though I have learned about it enough.   
     In my opinion, it is important to be a well-rounded person, and to take things seriously when they matter to you.  I tend to see things and think objectively, and sometimes I forget about other peopleï¿½s feelings while making my observations and decisions.  However, knowing how it feels to feel unimportant, I try to take care to not straight out offend someone else with my words.  I do take the philosophical road a lot of times; for example, I think religion is full of it, but I do believe that something is right for everyone, and you have to find within yourself what is right for you (ugh embarrassing).  I hate when people do not think that I am not competent, or underestimate my abilities.  This makes me want to prove myself, or avoid the person entirely.  I am usually pretty agreeable; I am willing to see the other side of the argument, and try to see where the other person(s) are coming from.  However, if a person is very disagreeable and despicable in my eyes, then I become very rigid, stubborn and disagreeable!   
     When I feel like there is a good cause, I am willing to go very far to help someone else out (if I have the means to).  I believe that there are rules that are made to protect certain principles and are truly in the best interest of everyone, and that there are rules to control people.  Either way, the more rules there are, the more rules there are to be broken!  I also strongly dislike when people have no regard towards life.  I donï¿½t mean that by like ï¿½oh my god, youï¿½re pro-choice?ï¿½.  What I mean by that is that people are so willing to throw away peoplesï¿½ (or animalsï¿½) well-being away.    This also makes me feel a strong sense of justice, and a desire to give it to those who suffer from injustice. ï¿½We have to pull the plug; why would anybody want to live like a vegetable?ï¿½ ï¿½The bills are too expensive; we can just get a new dogï¿½ ï¿½so what if he beats his girlfriendsï¿½ ass?  Guys do it all the timeï¿½ ï¿½ I tend to think that I have a very strong sense of justice, even if it means punishing those who I deem are ï¿½evilï¿½ to save those that I deem are ï¿½goodï¿½ (anybody watch The Green Mile?).  I usually tend to side with the vigilante as opposed to the police; sometimes, defying certain logic is the logical thing to do. 
     Some of the qualities I respect most in people are intelligence, being innovative, modesty, and having unconditional compassion for others (except when they donï¿½t deserve it).  I also respect people who show kindness to others; we donï¿½t know the battle people face every day, and we need to remember that before treating someone like shit just... because we can.

Last-Borns:Positives: Last-borns are the world's cheerleaders. You have strong people skills and love to entertain and talk to others. You make friends easily and immediately make others feel at home. You're an extrovert, energised by the presence of other people and you're probably not afraid to take risks.Negatives: Last-borns tend to get bored quickly. They have a strong fear of rejection and a short attention span. When the fun stops, they've had enough and want to check out. To some extent they're self-centred. They may harbour unrealistic expectations of finding a relationship that is always fun - and of course, such relationships simply do not last.Babies of the family are social and outgoing, they are the most financially irresponsible of all birth orders. They just want to have a good time. Knowing that these kids love the limelight, it's no surprise to discover that Billy Crystal, Goldie Hawn, Drew Carey, Jim Carey and Steve Martin are all lastborns.Popular wisdom says that the youngest ? who never quite shakes the role of being the baby of the family ? tends to be more free-spirited, adventurous, risky, and creative.Youngest siblings often don?t have as many care-taking responsibilities and may have more freedom to do things their own way.While lastborns may be charming, they also have the potential to be manipulative, spoiled or babied to the point of helplessness."The last born is the one who will probably still have a pet name although he's 29 and has a masters degree," Leman says.A lastborn who comes into a pack of already straight-and-narrow siblings might carve out her own niche by being more spunky and daring.

About:
Hi, my name is Tessa (you can call me Tess if you so choose) and I'm on this website to dig into my soul, man. Sort of. I'm a young 'un in the midst of high school. I'm going to be a writer when I'm older. (Though I'm technically one now, just not a *published* one.) One should note that in this I haven't necessarily guaranteed to be a SUCCESSFUL one, per se, but I certainly hope so, dude. 
However, with my arcane grammar knowledge (HEIL WEBSTER*), head full of ideas, and 100+ WPM, it seems that this is my fate; I feel most comfortable sitting at home, tinkering away on my laptop in a caffeinated daze while the rest of the world carries on with their business. That's just the way it is.  
I guess I don't really need to explain much about my personality, because I'm sure at this point you already know that I'm an eccentric, creative dreamer. But you won't know that I love cats and stuffed animals or that I enjoy playing the trombone.  And all animals, really are the bomb, except I don't really like bombs because they're all destructive and stuff. 
However, you probably could guess that I admire bassoons, and the flaming is in reference to their inherent coolness, not my secret desire to set them aflame and dance around the burning wood laughing maniacally. Did I just say that aloud? Freudian slip! (Flaming doesn't, incidentally, refer to a flamboyant gay man, although a gay bassoon is well within the realms of possibility because like, in German they're called "fagotts" or something, nuff said, plus you're blowing into a giant thing of wood. Homoerotic much?!?!?) 
On a related note, Freud is a really weird guy. Sure, he did set up the basis for modern psychology, but he was really weird. What's up with the Oedipus Complex anyway? Gross! At least I can blame his buddy Jung for coming up with the female variant, the Electra Complex. 
But the oboe is just a silly instrument. It's kind of annoying and goose-ish, even when played correctly. Don't tell any oboists that...I know one and they're quite sensitive folk, due to spending a majority of their time carving out wood and soaking it and stuff. I'd be crabby, too, if I was them. But I'm not. I'm a tromboner. (Hehehe boner. I need to stop spending time with 15 year old boys.)

About:
I suck at describing myself for the most part so read some nice things my friend says about me because these are facts ;) 
According to my friend;
Unbeknownst to her, she is a very diverse person, consisting of many personality traits. She is humble, goofy, brave, smart, wise, empathetic, and strong. She has faced adversity from a very young age and still has many challenges and struggles that effect her daily. However, she continues to fight and persevere because she is hopeful and goal oriented. 
These experiences have allowed her to develop a fascinating mind that is great at observing and breaking down situations. She is able to weigh all of the information and come to the best solution or the most moral conclusion. And when new information is added, she is completely capable of objectively deducing a new ideal from that additive construct. She is aware of the fact that she isn't perfect and always strives to better herself, as well as others. No matter the situation, she tries to build her friends up. Even when bringing forth a flaw within them, she is deeply concern for their well being and would take any criticisms in stride likewise. 
This is why she is such a wise and intelligent individual. You won't find her setting unrealistic standards for others as well as standards that are above her own.  
She is extremely goofy but in a fun and humorous way. If you're ever feeling down and need a pick-me-up, she's the one to see. She can give advice and empathize with your issues, and help you feel better when it's time to move forward. She has a big heart and anyone would be lucky to have a relationship with her, be it friendship or otherwise. 
She has many interests varying from music, to observation, to anime, learning, cartoons, mystery, and video games. The list goes on. However, she can talk about anything and keep the hype going regardless of the activity or subject. 
She is the girl next door, the moral compass, the wise familiar. She is the model-the blueprint-the template of what we consider a respectable and admirable human being. You will never feel unappreciated, forgotten or worthless when in her presence, because she is your devoted rock who is more patient and reliable than most. She makes the room brighter and your heart lighter. She is and will always be a kindred spirit.

I lurk in the Personality section.
I read a lot of threads, and I like to thank people for their posts.
Sometimes I get into moods where all I want to do is share everything about me, and I forget this is a public forum and anybody can read what I write.
Then I remind myself about so-called "internet anonymity"
Then I get into moods where I'm paranoid and want to delete everything I've ever written because it's all crap anyway, and Thanking becomes daunting. 
But mostly I read lots and lots of threads on everything.

...a mad scientist, a pre-med student, a psychological party-bag, a writer and spoken-word poet, a former death metal vocalist, an apatheist and existentialist, an impish anarchist (a.k.a. chaotic neutral), a rabid daydreamer, a collector of experiences, and a lover of all things strange, obscure, and beautifully horrifying. 
...My name is Skyler: I'm impulsive, an insomniac, and I am bad for my health. 
--I'm an adrenaline-junkie. Danger excites me.
--I am a synesthete (one who experiences synesthesia).
--I am prone to making an awkward situation worse. Sometimes on purpose. >_> I occasionally conduct little social experiments. Mostly because I often find the "social contract" to be... absurd... and in the way. 
--I do not think babies are cute. To me, they are odd, disproportionate, fleshy machines of secretion. 
--I am easily amused, but I am also easily bored. I invite you to shock me. Let's have a discussion. Make me question reality. Make me wonder, make me imagine. Make me think. Oh, how I love to think! I think about thinking. I think about all the processes involved in order for me to even be capable of thinking. I think about all the different sides of me inside my mind, my subconscious, and all the versions of me throughout my lifespan and growth and development, and all the differing things we've thought, or have yet to think, or would be thinking at this very moment. I think about the possibilities of time vortexes, and other universes, where perhaps there are many other alternate-timeline versions of me, and I wonder what we might be thinking, and if we're ever thinking the same thought at exactly the same point in time... or if our thoughts have ever slipped through to each other and entered another version's mind, and if that's what the feeling of deja-vu is... Or if we do have knowledge of each other's existence, but the knowledge is too intense or dangerous to retain, and so we are forced to forget... 
--I love star-gazing. Looking up at the night sky and seeing all those stars will never cease to fascinate me, no matter how many times I see it... It still never seems "ordinary." 
--I've been told that I have so many issues; I am Freud's wet dream.
--By far the most often thing ever said to me is something along the lines of, "Anyone ever tell you, you're weird?" ...It gets old after a while.
--I identify as gender-fluid, or gender neutral (meaning I feel neither male or female) and sometimes androgynous (meaning I feel both male and female). While I do feel more "masculine" than "feminine," and have always been "one of the guys," I do not feel as if I fit into either box. I don't like boxes, it's dark in there. 
--I find death to be one of the most fascinating aspects of life. Why? Because, as far as I know, death is the only experience I cannot acquire and then live to keep and reflect on. The complete separation of mind and body, as you're breaking away from the flesh-- what must it feel like? Death is the last big jump into the abyss. It is the unknown. It is the final adventure. Death is what makes life meaningful; if life just went on and on forever, then nothing would matter because we'd have endless amounts of time to do anything we'd ever want to do. But the clock is ticking...

I was brought up in a very poor Asian family and grew up in a poor neighborhood. I was abused as a child mentally, physically, and emotionally by my father. Along with poor personal decisions growing up (substance abuse, hanging with wrong crowd, etc.), I have become unstable in the mind. I am clinically depressed, have ADHD, and mild bipolar disorder. It really is a daily struggle for me to stay optimistic about life. 
However, as of now, I am trying to change my life around by separating my past and preventing it from affecting the current and future self. I feel like I have grown a lot these past few years; I am more confident in myself, openly interact with others, and enjoy the fine things in life from time to time. I am proud of how much I had overcome. However, I still often experience depressive episodes that seem to put me at a standstill in this world. I don't let that stop me though, because I know from experience that many of the problems I come across can be dealt with. 
I'm currently a university student studying in a business/IT program, although it is more like a fall-back choice. Honestly, I am more passionate about becoming a musician - and I am endlessly searching for opportunities to grow as one and possibly make it a career. 
According to various online tests, my personality type is an INFP. Although I highly agree with it often, I sometimes I feel that I am more of an INTP or INFJ, mostly because these two personality types really relate to me in regards to how connected I feel with the world and the deep desire I have to understand how the world works. I have tried to understand the 8 cognitive functions but constantly struggle having to choose between being an INFP, INTP, or INFJ. So, just for the sake of it I have decided officially to call myself an INFP. 
What do I like? Well... I like music. I like movies.  I love philosophy. I love astronomy. I love cosmology. And in regards to those last three, I like to ask questions about them because I am curious. It's interesting how beliefs are formed to understand the world and it intrigues me so much how vast this universe is, yet, is built from things smaller than atoms. Generally, anything that revolves around knowledge of the world sends me into deep thought. BUT... I will fall in love with you if you could hold up a conversation with me on cosmology and astronomy.  
I'M ALSO CRAZY ABOUT ALIENS AND UFOs. There, I said it. I'm a nut job. I'm open to talking about it, but I don't explicitly do unless the conversation steers towards that topic. So don't worry, I'm not that socially awkward. :) 
I am not religious, but for some reason I can't help but feel there is a divine being out there. I am perceptive about coincidences and derive special meaning out of things; almost to the point where someone might call me superstitious if I tell them my experiences. I really appreciate the beauty of the world... although it feels so hostile to me more often than not - as if I don't belong in this world. It makes me feel alone sometimes, and being a romanticist who is idealistic makes it that much more so.  
I value close relationships, but I get too emotionally attached to those I'm attracted to romantically. I get jealous a lot and become extremely upset when my love is not reciprocated almost, or just as strongly as how I express it. As often as I try not to think so, I feel that my past is eating away at my confidence and self-esteem and people can sense that around me - that although I may be a good person by nature, I am just unstable and cannot be helped. And that's understandable. It's emotionally exhausting and unhealthy for both parties. I yearn for a beautiful intimate relationship, but I know it is unwise to do so in my current state, unless I am willing to take chances and grow. 
I am random and quirky. I often sing (horribly), but you won't ever get to hear me sing unless I'm 100% comfortable with you or you catch me off guard. I'm usually soft-spoken when I'm in a neutral mood, but I can quickly become loud and ambitious when happy/excited, or irritable and mean after a certain point (this is where my bipolar disorder comes into play). I am obsessed with the correct use of grammar. Sadly, spoken language is not my skill. Although I can speak relatively fine, I often lose my train of thought and end up not making any sense. There were times where that, along with social anxiety, have gotten me into embarrassing situations. But in all honesty, I'm fine with it because at the end of the day it is experience to help me grow.  
Ways in which ADHD affects me: Again, losing train of thought. I often get bombarded with random thoughts. Despite all this creativeness I seem to have, I initiate projects but never finish them. I do multiple projects at once and rarely get the quality in the results I want. I am forgetful - often placing things down or thinking about something one minute, then the next minute forget where it was or what it was about. An extreme yet real example: Walking into a room to grab something only to forget why I went in there in the first place (it's a bit funny sometimes lol). I'm taking medication for it though and it helps me a lot; and although it has a lot of negative impacts on my life, it really does help me to be quick on my feet as well as makes me very imaginative and creative. Without it, I don't think I would have been this curious about the world we live in. 
Random facts: I enjoy composing music (wouldn't say I'm that good though). I'm currently learning how to play the guitar. I have a thing for girls who tie their hair up and I squirm like a child when I see a girl acting cute. Weird and immature, I know.

I was hatched from a beautiful gray egg in the dead of night, in the light of a full moon, in the stinking humidity of a Texas' summer breath, and the first thing I did was release a terrifying scream that shook the surrounding earth within a radius of 5 miles. Naturally, it shook me out of the tree and I landed on my head. Ever since then I just haven't been right. 
I was taken in by a family of wolves that had been roving around for a nice armadillo to snack on. They had thought it was me and proceeded to start chewing me, but I had the consistency of stringy melting rubber ball and they spit me out declaring I was the nastiest thing they've ever tasted. From that day forward I was a wolf. Everything they did, I was expected to do. Whatever they ate, I ate. Whatever they played, and bounced among them. Wherever they went, I waddled along right behind them. 
With time, I grew. Not much, but I did grow in many ways. My wiry body grew thicker and sharper. My fur turned into long, sleek feathers, which was worth the awkward bald patches I was heckled for for so long. My beak became hard, my claws sharp, my eyes keen. Though mainly innate, a large part of my wit was also strengthened by my little pack. We shared the desire to hunt, but they piqued my interest in not just tactics, but true strategy. How intrinsic I became when we discovered I was creature of flight. I wasn't an odd thing for me however, to smash my cranium into the nearest pine and send its bulky seeds scattering all over my brothers and send the prey running. In time though, I was soaring high and providing a good eye to my fellow hunters. Ah, the joy that floods back when I think of us all gathered around a slain doe, them ripping into the meat, me giving an occasional good tear with my hardy beak and leaning back to gulp it all down at once. Those days couldn't last forever though. 
One morning I had came across a curious little hole, so I shuffled around it and peered in. I didn't see anything inside so I paced around it five more times while looking around then stopped, looked down, then peered in again. Well, there was still nothing to see but the hole was beckoning me. So I stuck my head in it. 
It really wasn't the best decision to say the least, my head became stuck. I looked around a bit inside and shortly after realized I couldn't pull it back out. I pulled and twisted and shoved back and forth over and over. I screamed and cried and from the outside I'm sure it looked like a strange mating dance. So much time went by and I finally just relaxed all my muscles and let my body collapse outside the hole. My eyes started closing and right when I was about to completely doze off, something started sniffing my butt; but I recognize that snout anywhere--it was the very cub I had grown up with all these years--Snoofy! I cried out in joy and he bit my butt to my alarm. "You know me!" "I can't get you out any other way!" With that he continued tugging and pulling my body every which way. He then tried digging around me, dirt kept collapsing on my head but the ground was becoming loose.  
Suddenly a shout ran out and I heard a growl. Somebody screamed and something hit Snoofy, he let out a yelp and collapsed on my legs. Again, I was alone, ants picking my skin, a soaking wet butt with clumps of dirt from Snoofy's attempt to free me.  I heard more steps behind me. Little smooth hands picked dirt around and pulled
me out. I was happy to be free, but not to be in the clutches of a little human but I was helpless. I was weak and somewhat bent up, my eyes half open due to tears and chunks of dirt stuck in them. I could barely see the girl even with evening fast approaching.  
Somehow I ended up in her backpack, in a house, in an animal shelter, in a pile of balloons, on a cruise, and halfway around the world. She was nice as well as my other captors--but they had their own ends and I had to find my pack. I've since escaped my rescuer and others too, I've zipped through power lines and fought rats with sharp claws and whips for tails. I've had many good times too, and I've enjoyed my solitary travels more than many I've had with company--but I long for the night when I'm reunited with my pack and we can scream together to the moon.

The following description of the 379 was not written by me but taken from: https://www.facebook.com/Katherinefauvreconsulting/posts/1392449044409080 
The 379 
I call the 279 and the 379 the Rainbow Tritypes. They like colorful events, multi-colored images and colorful people. They are diverse and accepting and generally love people. 
These two Tritypes are very similar at first glance. However, the difference between the 3 and the 2 is important. The 279 is the most relational Tritype and the 379 is the most positive Tritype. 379s are even more positive that the 279s. They care about people like the 279 but focus more on their achievements. Both Tritypes avoid conflict and want to be upbeat...but how? 
The 279 needs easy relating and positive encounters...they try to smooth things over so people are happy and easier to be around. ;)) They focus on okness. 
The 379 needs to "be" an exemplar of what is positive. They are like a handful of colorful balloons. They also love images of rainbows and balloons regardless of what type leads. The 3 needs to be positive to be a success in the eyes of others...their can-do nature is motivated by what is positive to be liked. The 7 needs to be upbeat and is motivated by what is possible to be liked.The 9 needs to be comfortable and feels they must be kind and harmonious to be liked. 
So the 379 struggles when they have a disappointing experience and don't achieve their goal. They are quick to deny painful emotions in favor of pseudo happiness and turn lemons into lemonade more than any other Tritype. 
When they are down their world become bleak and gray. It is an opportunity for introspection and growth but for this Tritype it needs to be in small bites. 
So when a painful experience is chronic and needs time to heal the 379 can become impatient and very hard on themselves for being down. Like the balloons of happiness that become deflated,when in pain, the 379 can come across as shallow due to their effort to be positive when they are actually feeling despair and a sense of inner emptiness. They can feel like empty calories. 
They love people and the energy that comes from being connected to people. They like color in every form. Like flowers that turn to face the sun, 379s need the inspiration that comes from the positive feedback they receive for being good-natured. They are secretly very ambitious but seek affirmation in a quiet way. 
The 379 Tritype needs to be positive. They lose their motivation to be and become.They want success and to feel upbeat but also seek quiet stardom.

About:
Greetings Earthlings! So here's a bit about me.

When in a growth state, Type Sevens become focused like Type Fives. When they?re stressed, they become a perfectionist like a Type One. The enthusiastic nature of the Type Seven combines with the cooperative nature of the Type Six, making the 7w6 a very outgoing type. 
Your second type (your next strongest type) is Type 3 with a 4 wing: Type Three individuals are self-assured, confident, and driven for success. Type Threes have a great deal of energy that propels them to excel at their chosen field, and this is why the type is often called The Achiever. Although Threes may not always like it, they?re often looked up to. Type Threes, more than any other type, are the most likely to be a workaholic. Your third type (the least-used of the three) is Type 8 with a 7 wing: Eights are assertive, dominant individuals who naturally take control of situations. Eights are aggressive in satisfying their needs, and indeed, Type Eight is the most aggressive personality type in the Enneagram. When in a state of growth, Eights become like Type Twos - caring and protective of other people. When Eights are stressed, they become withdrawn and secretive like Type Fives. You're an Eight with a Seven wing, which means that the outgoing nature of Seven combines with the assertive nature of Type Eight to create one of the most dynamic types in the Enneagram. Type 8w7s are a force to be reckoned with.

About: I find that my interests cover this fairly well :)

Joined this forum when, after taking the Myers-Briggs test multiple times, I finally tested as an INFJ. This realisation was incredible for me, as I had recently gone through a huge upheaval in my life and was 'discovering myself.' By accepting the label of an INFJ, I am on my way to accepting who I am (even if it is extremely painful and complex at times!) This forum and those who upkeep it are hugely beneficial in this process, and for that I am grateful to everyone here. 
My life is currently in limbo. I am waiting to graduate; once I do, I will see if I will go into the corporate world or do something completely unexpected and wild. In the meantime, my mind is overheating. My brain is a pressure cooker full of vague feelings and ideas; once I have the time they will all be released! 
In the past I was a people-pleaser and a materialistic social butterfly. Now I realise that none of these labels suit me, so I am now a gentle soul that appreciates quiet and peace. My heart is full to the brim with empathy and care for others; love beams from my heart to those I have connected with. I wish I could curl up next to them and spend the rest of my life just being near them and enjoying their presence, like a little cat basking contentedly in the sunlight. My spirit is kind but my voice is LOUD about the issues I care about!  I aim to find beauty and meaning in all that I do. I hate writing about myself because i feel self-conscious. Every time I feel inspired to write, once I'm finished I immediately want to delete everything. I'm going to control that urge...now.

I think that personality theories are somewhat pseudo-scientific and should be explored lightly, but I do view them as useful tools for personal advancement and psycho-social understanding. While I feel that theories discussed here have potential to be used in egotistical ways that may be psychologically damaging, I think that the Enneagram is useful in identifying the motivations and poisonous thoughts (as a key founder stated them) that drive people and are particularly helpful for spiritual :P advancement, but in a less concrete way as explained by the overall theory itself, and that the MBTI is valuable in identifying how people interact and view themselves socially. Individuals are immensely more complex than can be explained by a central instinct/fear or guiding 'cognitive function'. Although they should be taken lightly, I do think theories such as the MBTI, Socionics and the Enneagram are nonetheless useful as indicators of personality and (more importantly) as methods of understanding psychological problems, and I am grateful that places like personalitycafe exist as open and understanding arenas of exploration in the human psyche.  
Nonetheless:
Enneagram: Either 5w4 or 7w6 core, followed by 1w9 and 4w3 in preference

I have had a strong interest in both the MBTI and Enneagram for a good twenty five years. There is alway more to learn and just as much to try and recall. I am interested in the nuances of the nine energies and the Instinctual energies and recently I have begun to explore the math related to the enneagram symbol. If you do not want what I want, please try not to tell me that my want is wrong.  
Or if my beliefs are different from yours, at least pause before you set out to correct them. 
Or if my emotion seems less or more intense than yours, given the same circumstances, try not to ask me to feel other than I do. 
Or if I act, or fail to act, in the manner of your design for action, please let me be. 
I do not, for the moment at least, ask you to understand me. That will come only when you are willing to give up trying to change me into a copy of you. 
If you will allow me any of my own wants, or emotions, or beliefs, or actions, then you open yourself to the possibility that some day these ways of mine might not seem so wrong, and might finally appear as right?for me. To put up with me is the first step to understanding me. 
Not that you embrace my ways as right for you, but that you are no longer irritated or disappointed with me for my seeming waywardness. And one day, perhaps, in trying to understand me, you might come to prize my differences, and, far from seeking to change me, might preserve and even cherish those differences. 
I may be your spouse, your parent, your offspring, your friend, your colleague. But whatever our relation, this I know: You and I are fundamentally different and both of us have to march to our own drummer.

Every encounter in life can be meaningful if you make it that way.

About:
I'm into weird, unconventional things (I'm perfectly ok w/ this); if you're not, no one's telling you that you have to be my friend. To me, a lot of traditional views are either a. lacking character/downright boring; b. no longer apply to the ever-changing world; c. something I find myself disagreeing with a lot; or d. I think there's a better fashion in how to run the show. There are few traditions in this world that I know of with which I see eye-to-eye but don?t feel like discussing here, as my profile would become more of a novel than a brief idea of who I am as a person. 
I don't care about socializing with a lot of people if I find them to be some sort of incompetent fool or I'm just awkward around them because I'm not comfortable around them; either one of those two or it's just that no one around cares to talk about things I enjoy discussing.  
I am a pretty accepting and understanding person for the most part, but this does NOT mean I am going to accept everything someone says or does. Also, this does not mean that I am going to be accepting of everyone. What this means is that I am open to others' views if they're credible to me. It is all about HOW you present your views to me, not so much WHAT your views are. So, if you find yourself wondering why I turned your views away without question or am "being stubborn and not listening to your so called 'wisdom'", you can count on that being why.  
I like arguing for the sakes of arguing! This is because I can be a competitive person. No, I?m not all into physical competition but rather I like intellectual discussions or even debates? as long as I know what the hell I?m talking about in regards to the topic at hand (and related things of course).  
If there's one thing that REALLY sickens me about people the most, it's short-sightedness. Again, everyone slips up here and there, perhaps they will do something impulsive or just downright idiotic; even I don't always think things through all the way (no one does 100% of the time). Those who just can't think about the future at all are the ones that I just can't get along with one bit. Even though I like to think of past memories, I LOVE to ponder about the possibilities, and in that the future a lot more than I show/discuss.  
One day, I want to invent something that will improve the quality of life for the human population (I have some ideas that I don't want to share on here :P). In this, I highly value innovation and creativity because I feel that without those 2 things, we would still be in the stone age to this day and people would still live only until they are 35 years old or so.  
I also value mental competence. Ok, I understand that people, including myself, make silly mistakes and do stupid things; however, if one is intelligent enough, I feel that they will be able to learn from their mistakes and change for the future to prevent further mistakes of similar or the same nature. If you cannot learn from your own mistakes at all or just don?t care to do so, then I do not wish to associate myself with you. In other words, I get uptight with truly stupid people. 
Another thing I highly value in myself along with others is the ability to understand him-or-herself (introspection). When I get to know people, they really should know who they are as a person. It may take some thinking but it?s not really hard to understand why you: are interested in the things you are; are attracted to the people you?re attracted to; why you feel the way you do about some things or why you?re in a particular mood; why you think the way you do; why you perceive things the way you do; etc. 
It really disappoints me when I?m trying to get to know someone by asking questions such as ?why do you like that?? and all they say is ?because I just do?. How do you expect others to know you if you don?t even know you? It?s pretty ridiculous to expect others to understand you if you don?t understand yourself.  
In my personal opinion, lying about who you are/not being yourself is downright pointless to me; if you're lying to protect yourself or someone else, it's one thing (if it?s a good cause done for a good reason). Otherwise, you're lying to yourself in the end.  
I do not respond in a particularly desirable way to others attempting to control me via testing my guilt or fear factors. Many people have tried to control me by trying to place guilt or fear on me and believe me they didn't get the results they liked. I am not one to be controlled anyways, although I can follow rules if they are logical and just make sense to me. As I like to say, others may steer the boat but only I am the captain to my ship. 
Another thing that really bothers me about some people is when they feel the need to use ?sophisticated? vocabulary terms in casual conversation. When I think of socializing with others in a casual setting, you should be on the same page. Save the whole competition thing for circumstances where there is reason to be competitive. If you?re trying to impress others with your vocabulary and thus trying to look more educated than those you are socializing casually with, that to me shows insecurity and shows that person?s inability to hold a real conversation with others. No wonder people don?t like being around those type of people. If you?re like that, no wonder people don?t like you! That?s how I feel about it anyways.   
If/when I find someone I want to be with for the rest of my life or at least a pretty long time, I really do hope that this person knows how to manage their time properly and learns that work/school isn't their whole life. I mean honestly, if you expect someone to understand you care about them and such, make some effort to spend quality time together. I find it so funny when people decide to get married, yet when they spend little time together they wonder why their marriage life sucks so much @$$. 
Also, I need someone who is going to be able to have the time or at least be able to MAKE the time to give me a call not just send a text message or when they know I'm upset to actually tend to me right then and there, not holding onto that thought until they're done with work or school or even a game. I'm sorry but making someone wait for comfort and love is just so loser-like. Just sayin'. 
Well I'm not sharing my whole life story on here. So if you'd like to get to know me, message me on here.

Evil is a Passionate Lover   
Finished with sadness,
I turn my Soul from familiar smells
And Primal comforts.
Fight the overwhelming pull
Of Habit and Time,
perfumed smoke, casual stomping
of unripened worth,
sexual awareness before awareness of sex. 
Come here, child. Learn from me.
Don't lie there and barter dignity for touch,
holiness for a momentary tribute to existence.
Sanctity for seminal fluid, and obstinate callouses. 
Run your mental fingers over the back of my experience.
Feel the welts. Slowly...Yes. Oh,That, that was a bad one. ..
Time has changed their appearance.
But I have changed their effect.
Dwell on the pain but briefly,
for I have high hopes for you, my child. 
Be afraid of evil. It does exist.
Into His eyes I looked .
Inhuman slits of black.
You think I jest?!
When the eyes become coal,
there is no more pleading,
There is no human behind the mask.
The Pain will now commence.
By what machinations?
He swirls up your body like sensuous smoke,
then materializes
with a death grip on your heart.

I know there are some who pull pranks on each other and some who just bully and ridicule for no good reason. I don't like pranks or bullying and neither does my bro so we look out for each other instead. I don't normally call him "bro" though, but in this case it's a nice subsitute. Why is my computer still loading it's been on for five hours!!! How I love/hate technology. I joined personality cafe because I thought I could learn more about my thoughts as well as other personality types. I prefer these kinds of labels rather than the dreadful stereotypes society makes out of nowhere. I still have faith in the human race, but as for reality tv I've completely given up. So after taking three tests I discovered I'm an INFP which means I got my head and feet in the clouds, I'm creative, and I like to help people. Very true. That's not all that's just the bare bones of INFP's if you want to learn more you should look it up if you're interested. If you want to ask me a question about INFP's or something of the like you can message me if you want but keep it appropriate please. About:
"There are stars in my mind. One of them has fallen and ignited a burning fire in my heart. It's set ablaze the garden in my soul...   
It has fallen to ash... 
...And the butterflies in my stomach are starving.  
They'd much better be moths drawn to the blaze...  
Tell me-- is this how the fleeting saturniidae are born?"   
                                          -(modified) poem by me     
Hello, there. The name's Dea (Day-uh), if you don't feel like constantly pronouncing the scientific name of a moth family.  ;) 
Feel free to chat if you'd like. I promise, I'm friendly. Though if you can't handle a bit of weird, you may want to reconsider socializing with me.  
Anyway, I'm here because I've developed a heavy interest in psychological traits and behavior, and enjoy finding ways to connect them. 
One thing I must emphasize about myself-- 
I am never done learning.  
Research is my foundation. I have a heavy obsession with statistics and charts. In this regard, I view it as art, and art, in turn, becomes the artist. This is an unending mutuality.  
I have plenty of other interests too. I love nature and value solitude (to the point that it might as well be a long-term hobby). I also enjoy dissecting and repairing broken electronics. I'm certified in PC repair.  
Hey, we all have that one 'off' interest.  
Though, warning--whatever you have to say to me has the potential to fall victim to a ~90% chance of being over-analyzed, sifted, filtered, and steeped, being saved for that one ridiculously improbable situation I might encounter where what I've learned might actually make a constructive impact while the blatant every-day chance to use it goes over my head while I'm busy with self-reflecting and hermitizing. 
In other words.... my analytical tendency is evil.   
Now that that's out of the way, if you still care to chat, have at it. If you have any questions, ask. Don't be afraid to. I generally answer, but I'd probably die if I had to be the one to initiate the conversation.  
Well, beyond this point, I'm not quite sure what to say, so I'll list some of my favorite quotes:  
?My friend, I am not what I seem. Seeming is but a garment I wear ? a care-woven garment that protects me from thy questionings and thee from my negligence.
The ?I? in me, my friend, dwells in the house of silence, and therein it shall remain forever more, unperceived, unapproachable.? -Kahlil Gibran 
"Look like th' innocent flower, But be the serpent under 't." -Macbeth  
--

I'm an inked moto-girl. I ride a Kawasaki Ninja 300 alongside my husband who rides a Kawasaki Ninja 636. I listen to a healthy mix of classic, alternative and indie rock. Foo Fighters, Muse, Metallica, Nirvana, Godsmack, Rammstein, Eminem, Rihanna, Red Hot Chili Peppers, Coldplay to name a few. 
I appreciate the finer things in life; luxury shoes and accessories namely. Christian Louboutin, Hermes, Chanel, and Cartier are my favourite designer houses. My personal fashion style is classic with an edge - clean lines, textures, spikes, leather, buckles, and most types of hardware. My favourite colour is gold, though, blood red is also acceptable (blood is the new pink), followed by other jewel tones of deep green, purple or blue. 
I am a mother to a boy and a master to two lovable but very carnivorous felines. I'm a huge advocate of raw-feeding for both cats and dogs, without exception. That's right, my cats eat flesh and bones on the daily.  
I enjoy TV and movies, dining out, and retail therapy as a typical city girl does. But, in the summer, I love to fish, camp, go on road trips, and explore nature. I also happen to be a geek. I used to play MMORPGs and other video games religiously and spent several years as a gamemaster to a large community and forum-modded on several sites. I enjoy a broad spectrum of game genres (a few titles to note: Quake 2, Halo, Starcraft, Command and Conquer, Ragnarok Online, The Sims, and a crapton of Facebook/phone games). Additionally, I take strategy board and card games very seriously, especially ones that require tactical thinking and cooperative play (bonus if its difficult to win). These are but all tools to develop my skills. At the moment, I am playing Mafia on PerC to work on my Ni. I enjoy leadership roles as moderator or gamemaster holding community events and enforcing policy. 
When it comes to media, I can't get enough of endless suffering. Catharsis is huge for me. Shows like Game of Thrones, Sons of Anarchy, Downton Abbey and The Walking Dead are right up my alley. I look for unpredictable plot, realistic characters, and power plays. My favourite characters are usually strong and polarizing: Cersei Lannister, Tywin Lannister, Daenerys Targaryen, Lady Olenna (Game of Thrones); The Governor, Carol (The Walking Dead), Tara Knowles (Sons of Anarchy), Lagertha (Vikings), Lady Mary Crawley (Downton Abbey), Cristina Yang (Grey's Anatomy), Charlotte King (Private Practice), Dottie Underwood, Agent Carter (Agent Carter). I generally enjoy period dramas. 
I describe myself as independent, reliable, and efficient. But if you're unlucky (or a moron), then I will be unabashedly condescending, cruel and judgmental. I am a feminist and I am passionate about reproductive rights, gender equality, affirmative action and other social justice issues. Additionally, I am ambitious and believe in follow-through.  I have little respect for those who don't. 
I do not tolerate the below traits very well, so it be best to stay out of my way if it applies to you:
- inefficiency

- trolling
- tardiness
- excuses and apologies
- being too sensitive
- indecisiveness
- lack of follow through and flakiness
- smokers/recreational drug users of any kind

- inability to see one's own racist/sexist biases 
Do not waste my time. 
Stop whining and suck it up.

If you need to know anything about God, it's that he loves you more than you will ever be able to know or understand, and he is able and willing to rescue you, and to know and be known by you, because of what his Son has done for you, and for all of us. 
Joy is free and available, if you will accept it.  If you don't, I won't think less of you.  I just desperately hope, for your sake, that you understand what you're walking away from before you say no.  Jesus's call is not to be taken lightly. 
Thanks for taking the time to read this, and God bless you.

About: Like their fellow SPs, ISTPs are fundamentally Performers (note the capital 'P' :-)), but as Ts their areas of interest tend to be mechanical rather than artistic like those of ISFPs, and unlike most ESPs they do not present an impression of constant activity. On the contrary, they lie dormant, saving their energy until a project or an adventure worthy of their time comes along--and then they launch themselves at it. The apparently frenzied state that inevitably ensues is actually much more controlled than it appears--ISTPs always seem to know what they're doing when it comes to physical or mechanical obstacles--but the whole chain of events presents a confusing and paradoxical picture to an outsider.ISTPs are equally difficult to understand in their need for personal space, which in turn has an impact on their relationships with others. They need to be able to "spread out"--both physically and psychologically--which generally implies encroaching to some degree on others, especially if they decide that something of someone else's is going to become their next project. (They are generally quite comfortable, however, with being treated the same way they treat others--at least in this respect.) But because they need such a lot of flexibility to be as spontaneous as they feel they must be, they tend to become as inflexible as the most rigid J when someone seems to be threatening their lifestyle (although they usually respond with a classic SP rage which is yet another vivid contrast to their "dormant," impassive, detached mode). These territorial considerations are usually critical in relationships with ISTPs; communication also tends to be a key issue, since they generally express themselves non-verbally. When they do actually verbalize, ISTPs are masters of the one-liner, often showing flashes of humor in the most tense situations; this can result in their being seen as thick-skinned or tasteless.Like most SPs, ISTPs may have trouble with rote and abstract classroom learning, which tend not to be good measures of their actual intelligence. They tend, sometimes with good reason, to be highly skeptical of its practical value, and often gravitate towards classes in industrial arts; part-time vocational/ technical programs can be useful to even the college-bound ISTP. In terms of careers, mechanics and any of the skilled trades are traditional choices, and those ISTPs with strong numerical as well mechanical gifts tend to do extremely well in most areas of engineering. Working as paramedics or firefighters can fulfill the ISTP need to live on the edge; they are at their best in a crisis, where their natural disregard for rules and authority structures allows them to focus on and tackle the emergency at hand in the most effective way.ISTPs with more sedate careers usually take on high-risk avocations like racing, skydiving, and motorcycling. While aware of the dangers involved, they are so in touch with the physical world that they know they can get away with much smaller safety margins than other types.

Love, it never dies, it never goes away, it never fades, so long as you hang onto it. I have dreams, small dreams, nothing big and out there. But they are something I know one day will be a reality, as some of them already are. Im proud of the person I am, proud of the things I have, and grateful for the people in my life. I stand up for what I believe in, I dont conform to fit in, and I speak my mind when necessary( and sometimes when it isnt) Im stubborn, have very little patience, hate admitting Im wrong, and I let my feelings get hurt way to easily. But hey Im not perfect and atleast I can admit that. I have an amazing husband, Corey Hunnicutt,  hes the absolute best thing to have ever happened to me. He saved me when I desperately needed it, and gave me a family that I adore and couldnt be more thankful for. I could go on and on about him, but this is About me, not him. lol. I tend to ramble about the things I love. I consider myself an artsy person, I love decorating, drawing, painting, designing, etc. It makes me happy (among other things). Im a nerd, and proud of it. I could sit and play a good RPG or shooter game for hours. I love taking care of people, being able to fix them some food give them a place to stay or just some advice, knowing that I have helped them in some way brings me a sense of contentment, & saying that, if you ever want to chat or vent, Im a good listener. Just shoot me a msg:) But a guess this is all I have to say. All I have to offer is myself and nothing more.

About: "A few details"? If you know an ENTJ, you know that's impossible. Well, I'm very intense, interested in all sorts of things from science to Christianity to Science Fiction to discussing principles and concepts to English (I teach English to my pastor's grandchildren). And I discover something new about my own language frequently (did you know there is a rule about how you pronounce "ed" at the end of a past-tense word? I didn't either until 5-6 years ago). I love airplanes and trains (should I add automobiles to match the movie???) I love architecture, especially here in Guadalajara, Mexico. I love to travel but don't get around easily like I used to. I've been in 34 countries, 39 American states (not counting being in an airport), and 17 Mexican states. I'm interesting, intelligent, uber-outgoing (no surprise to you), funny, even silly sometimes, intellectual, glass 3/4 full person but am learning to see the negative side of things when necessary, intensely interested in people. I love to read. Current favorite author is Diana Gabaldon who writes the Outlander books (now a series on Starz), but read in many genres and types (science, Christian, psychology, etc. etc.) of writings--even cereal boxes if you put one in front of me. I'm constantly reading Spanish signs out loud when going down the street--much to the chagrin of my bi-lingual taxi driver, or the puzzlement of the neighbor I walk by. Used to play volleyball and was pretty good for a 5'2" (now more like 5') woman. I love to walk though my body does NOT agree with that statement.Travel, reading, plants, CSI type shows (fav is NCIS), actually, too many to list.

About: I am constantly preoccupied with many different ideas and thoughts, some of which are nonsensical, others are quite grounded.  These ideas range from economics to relationships to morality to philosophy and to religion. I have been told that I speak like was born in the 1950?s or earlier since I tend to like to use proper language. It?s difficult to explain but I like the idea of being a proper gentlemen and appearing to be proper though I am not always as such. There is an appeal to being well dressed, having complementing and nice jewelry, hair done and bit of facial scruff while also having tattoos and what might be considered really liberal ideas for my stuffy and proper appearance. If I had to limit myself to one outfit for the rest of my life, it would be without a doubt, a suit. I care about my appearance and I have no shame in admitting it. At the same time, I don?t place a tremendous amount of value or confidence in my appearance. It only serves to compliment what I believe to be my greatest asset; my mind. I don?t consider myself to be naturally intelligent or necessarily gifted. What I am is curious and creative. I am always exploring, learning and expanding my knowledge base. I don?t take being wrong as an insult but instead an opportunity to grow my perspective. It is this that makes me believe that my mind is a special thing. I don?t start a discussion with the hopes of winning said discussion; I do so with the hope of expanding my perspective.This all being said, I have been known to have a dominating presence at times. I will play devil?s advocate and argue points I don?t necessarily believe because I think it is ignorant to ignore other perspectives simply because we disagree with them. Also, outright statements lacking in fundamental truth bother me and I will call them out. I cannot tolerate ignorance but will endure it if I must for the learning experience. Don?t let any of this scare you though, once you get past my demeanor, I am actually a panda bear. Give me good food, something fuzzy and cuddly and I will be grinning for days. One of my favorite movies all time is Kung Fu Panda for a reason. I take myself both very seriously and not serious at all. I am an outspoken nerd who loves all things nerdy and geeky. I am frequently found working on one art project or another. About: I'm an INTP and consistently test as such. I'm less interested in the enneagram but I've tested both as a 5w6 and a 9, which means I'm likely the former (in any case, very conflict avoidant). I can see both sides of most arguments, but am dismissive of emotional reasoning except when I can see its relevance. I consider myself extremely skeptical, although I maintain tact and try not to push my opinions on others, but will freely share them when prompted (I have many, but few of them are hardened). This being said, I am also skeptical of Jungian psychology and the like, but from a social perspective I think typology is very useful for understanding possible thought processes and points of view of others. I've decided to join this forum because I find some of the conversations really interesting and am hoping to learn more about how myself and others function in a broad sense, and maybe improve my social skills (I sometimes have trouble with new people).To go over my profile in a bit more detail, I suffer from social anxiety and depression, but am still very much capable of functioning well socially when I am at social gatherings. However, I'm also capable of playing up parts of my personality to be the person certain people will like, so I'm kind of this paradoxically reclusive social chameleon. People really seem to like me, but even when the feeling is mutual I often have difficulty reaching out to them.I am a left-wing, homosexual, cisgendered, agnostic male from southern Ontario. I am the youngest of several siblings, and generally have very mixed emotions about most people, especially my own family members. I am two years into a very happy relationship with an INFJ. I am an awful procrastinator, but usually able to get high grades anyway. Recently, I left my country's top university 2/3 through my BA to pursue a career in welding. I was originally hoping to be a copy editor or librarian, but after meeting people in those fields I could tell I wasn't interested in the stress of competing for very rare positions and then, if successful, constantly fearing my job being declared excess. I like RPGs and music, playing a few instruments privately and singing, and listening to lots of sad indie music, psychedelic rock, funk, and all their offshoots. Theres more I could say, but I shouldn't blather on anymore.Functionally,I fluctuates from slightly to fairly stronger than E.N is consistently quite stronger than ST is slightly to moderately stronger than FP is always extremely higher than J - usually over 90%.
