About: You are a Type 4 with a 5 wing: "The Bohemian"Your trifix is 4w5, 6w5, 1w9.In enneagram theory, you have one type for how you relate to the world (either 8, 9, or 1), one type for how you think (5, 6, 7) and one type for how you see yourself (2, 3, 4.) Your tri-fix contains one number from each of these triads. They are listed in the order of how strongly they present in your personality. Your core type (your strongest type) is Type 4 with a 5 wing: Type Four individuals are intensely emotionally aware, and often retreat to their rich inner world of concepts and ideas. They are the most artistic type in the Enneagram and driven to create their own, unique identity. Type Fours value authenticity highly and express themselves whenever they can. They are one of the most individualistic types in the Enneagram. Type Fours, when in a state of growth, become principled like Type Ones. When stressed, Type Fours can become clingy like an unhealthy Type Two. You are a Type Four with a Five wing, which means that the individualist nature of a Four combines with the cerebral nature of a Five to make you one of the most creative types in the Enneagram.Your second type (your next strongest type) is Type 6 with a 5 wing: Type Six individuals are reliable, committed, and security-oriented. They are natural troubleshooters, and are always aware of potential problems. This makes the Type Six anxious, but the anxiety fuels them to resolve their problems. They can range from loyal to rebellious, depending on where they get their security from ? if the security is from within, they can be very defiant? if it comes from others, they can be very cooperative and devoted. When a Type Six is in a growth state, they become calm like a Type Nine. When they are stressed, they can become arrogant like an unhealthy Type Three. You are a Type Six with a Five wing, which means that the committed nature of the Six combines with the cerebral nature of the Type Five. As a result, you often excel at concrete thinking and troubleshooting.Your third type (the least-used of the three) is Type 1 with a 9 wing: Type One individuals have a very finely tuned sense of right and wrong, and they chart the course of their lives by following a righteous path. This doesn?t have to be religious? it can be any set of principles that the Type One finds ethical. Ones are perfectionists, often setting high standards for themselves and others. Type One may very well be the most noble type in the Enneagram. When a Type One is in a state of growth, they become excited and joyous like a Seven. When a Type One is stressed, they become emotional and overwhelmed like an unhealthy Type 4. You are a Type One with a Nine wing, which means that the righteous traits of a Type One combine with the peaceful nature of the Type Nine to create a very idealistic personality.Some words that describe you: principled, moralistic, perfectionist, self-critical, creative, unique, authentic, emotional, loyal, reliable, anxious, skeptical.

About: If you're curious, my name mean here and there, or throughout; frequently. It is a first/second declension adverb in Latin that stems from the perfect passive participle of pando, or to spread (outwards)/unfold.In books, its used to allude to that a reference that can be found in various areas of a text. Though passim itself can be used in english on its own, the phrase sic passim (so throughout) is more commonly used in order to indicate that an idea or a word is found in various areas of an author's work. I uh....meant to use sic passim , but forgot to write sic when registering for my account. I had to reload the page a bunch of times since captcha wasn't working correctly (even though I swear I was correct in writing progressive like 10 times! About: Personal ~* Name - What do you preferred to be called? Just call me riza. - Any nicknames?* Male/Female/Trans? MaleLocation - Where were you originally born? Where do you live today? Any interesting story behind that? United States- If you could get up and go anywhere in the world at the present moment, where would you go and why? Not necessarily at the present moment, but in a few years I would like to travel to Japan and some countries in Scandinavia (after I learn more of their respective languages).Age - How old are you? Do you think you act your age? If not, explain which age you think you resemble most. Do it for the laughs. Within the stereotypical college age range. As with most people around my age, I also believe that I act older than my age, probably around 5-10 years older since I tend to associate most closely with teachers, some graduate students (PhD), and professors.Personal(ity) ~* What is your Myers-Briggs personality type and for how long have you been reading on personality theory? INTJ* What type do you usually test as? INFJ, since they generally confuse my relatively high Fi.* What are your favorite and least favorite personality types to be around? I'm not entirely sure, but for favorites, I think I work best with INFJs and INFPs. I have gotten along with with ESFJs. I tend to be indifferent towards the others, but I have had some conflicts with ISTJs and an ENFJ. I wouldn't want to generalize these though.If you've taken any other personality tests, included but not limited to tests like the Enneargram and Big 5 (SLOAN), what were your results?Enneagram - 4w5 Occupation ~* Employed or Unemployed? I'm a studentWhat is your education? In college, tell us your major. Engineering and STSWhat is your dream job? Professor, preferably in the humanities About You ~* Tell us in a brief paragraph or two how you would describe yourself and what you hope to get out of this forum.I've lurked around on these forums for a while and thought that I should just join. Though generally rather reserved, I try to make myself stand out in subtle ways, such as my appearance, my motivations, and my disposition towards trying new things. Because academia is rather competitive to enter, I attempt to use every tool that I discover to push my limitations; I tend to devalue innate ability. I love exploring the human condition and how we build knowledge around it.Yet, at the same time, differentiating myself can become quite alienating and makes it difficult for me to learn about other people, which tends to be a large source of my emotional energy. I joined PerC in hopes of meeting new people and potentially forming some friendships. Whether or not a person agrees with me on issues doesn't matter to me, I tend to care more about their temperament and outlook on life. Uniqueness generally piques my interest. In general, I am a rather serious person, which can sometimes grind against most of my college peers. I generally have to wear masks to efficiently communicate, and my hope would be to not have to do so here.Other ~What is your favourite section at the toy-store? I don't recall the last time that I visited a toy store.Do you collect anything? Scarves, in particular those made of cotton and viscose, rayon is okay too. Being a male and wearing scarves as part of my fashion makes me more memorable.What are your phobias? Acrophobia, arachnophobia, entomophobia.Describe your favourite food until you drool. Food tastes rather bland in general to me, but I like tofu, curry, and pho (and similar noodle soup dishes)Some of the things that you give you jollies? Talking to people about their futures and motivations or about humanity.What are your top five pet peeves? 1. Using popularity as a justification.2. Not necessarily a pet peeve, but I feel anguish whenever someone emphasizes a lack of innate ability or opportunity as a primary reason for not trying something.3. When people tell me to cut my hair! It's currently shoulder length, and I'm growing it out at the moment.4. Smugness and humble bragging generally rub me the wrong way.5. Whenever people cite money as their primary motivation for their pursuits.Extra! When people make assumptions regarding my (or others'!) gender or sexuality based on appearance. I generally frown upon labels of feminine being characteristic of women or masculine as being characteristic of men.What would a perfect day be like for you? Meeting and spending a day talking with a new friend (a lifelong friend, preferably).Do you prefer a vegetarian or meat diet or both? I'm not vegetarian, but I don't eat too much meat.Other Other ~ Yay or Nay?God and Souls Yay, with some nuances.The Death Penalty Yay, with reservations.Premarital Sex Indifferent.People are inherently good Yay.Destiny Nay.Done drugs Nay.Kissed in the rain Nay, and probably would move towards shelter first.Re-reading a good book Yay. Not limited to books; I will rewatch good shows or movies.

Moments of magic will glow in the night All fears of the forest are gone But when the morning breaks they're swept away by golden drops of dawn, of changes. Passions will part to a strange melody. That's just the way it is. I guess I don't really need to explain much about my personality, because I'm sure at this point you already know that I'm an eccentric, creative dreamer. But you won't know that I love cats and stuffed animals or that I enjoy playing the trombone.  And all animals, really are the bomb, except I don't really like bombs because they're all destructive and stuff.However, you probably could guess that I admire bassoons, and the flaming is in reference to their inherent coolness, not my secret desire to set them aflame and dance around the burning wood laughing maniacally. Did I just say that aloud? Freudian slip! (Flaming doesn't, incidentally, refer to a flamboyant gay man, although a gay bassoon is well within the realms of possibility because like, in German they're called "fagotts" or something, nuff said, plus you're blowing into a giant thing of wood. It's kind of annoying and goose-ish, even when played correctly. Don't tell any oboists that...I know one and they're quite sensitive folk, due to spending a majority of their time carving out wood and soaking it and stuff. I'd be crabby, too, if I was them. About: Self discovery is a hell of a drug, one that causes me to over analyze things too often to admit. For a long time I was convinced I was an INFP because of several poorly written profiles that convinced me that my misery was not my own fault. Which in retrospect was horrible both for myself as well as anyone else who identified as an INFP because of it. Let alone actual INFPs who had to live with such awful characterizations!Anyway, I'm rambling. My apologies. If you're actually reading this, you have my compliments. I'm simply a man who wants everyone in my life to be okay. I'm willing to work hard to see that it happens, but the truth I learned a long time ago is that the only person who can save you is yourself. It doesn't stop me from trying, however. I'm also an animal lover. I've been around livestock (particularly cattle) all of my life. No, I don't eat beef. I've seen too many animals I cared for deeply pass in unpleasant ways (despite my best efforts; such is the brutal truth of farm life, I'm afraid) and have no desire to eat beef as a result. I do, however, really really really love cheese. A lot. Honestly, want to get me started rambling again? Ask me something cheese-esque.Where was I?Oh, anyway, I was featured in an NPR piece on Millenials last year. Even got to close out the radio segment with a quote I gave. It made me feel rather special, though horribly embarrassed by how much I heard my voice quiver. What can I say? I'm a raging perfectionist, especially when it's myself involved.I occasionally blog, though not as often as I like. I also tweet quite regularly. Facebook concerns me, what with the violation of basic privacies and all that. Someday I plan on ruling the world just long enough to take brutal and efficient revenge on everyone and everything that hurt those that I care about, or those who hurt or abuse the poor or weak. It'll be an amazing few months, but I promise you won't be disappointed.Peace and love, y'all.Reading, Writing, Games, Gardening, ATVing, Theater

About: 3w2-7w8-9w8The following description of the 379 was not written by me but taken from: https://www.facebook.com/Katherinefauvreconsulting/posts/1392449044409080The 379I call the 279 and the 379 the Rainbow Tritypes. They like colorful events, multi-colored images and colorful people. They are diverse and accepting and generally love people.These two Tritypes are very similar at first glance. However, the difference between the 3 and the 2 is important. The 279 is the most relational Tritype and the 379 is the most positive Tritype. 379s are even more positive that the 279s. They care about people like the 279 but focus more on their achievements. Both Tritypes avoid conflict and want to be upbeat...but how?The 279 needs easy relating and positive encounters...they try to smooth things over so people are happy and easier to be around. ) They focus on okness.The 379 needs to "be" an exemplar of what is positive. They are like a handful of colorful balloons. They also love images of rainbows and balloons regardless of what type leads. The 3 needs to be positive to be a success in the eyes of others...their can-do nature is motivated by what is positive to be liked. The 7 needs to be upbeat and is motivated by what is possible to be liked.The 9 needs to be comfortable and feels they must be kind and harmonious to be liked.So the 379 struggles when they have a disappointing experience and don't achieve their goal. They are quick to deny painful emotions in favor of pseudo happiness and turn lemons into lemonade more than any other Tritype.When they are down their world become bleak and gray. It is an opportunity for introspection and growth but for this Tritype it needs to be in small bites.So when a painful experience is chronic and needs time to heal the 379 can become impatient and very hard on themselves for being down. Like the balloons of happiness that become deflated,when in pain, the 379 can come across as shallow due to their effort to be positive when they are actually feeling despair and a sense of inner emptiness. They can feel like empty calories.They love people and the energy that comes from being connected to people. They like color in every form. Like flowers that turn to face the sun, 379s need the inspiration that comes from the positive feedback they receive for being good-natured. They are secretly very ambitious but seek affirmation in a quiet way.The 379 Tritype needs to be positive. They lose their motivation to be and become.They want success and to feel upbeat but also seek quiet stardom.Everything.

I would also love to travel the world as travel nurse.I was raised in a cult known as the Jehovah's Witnesses, but after I saw flaws in their teachings, the Watchtower Society lost its hold over me. Now, I am free to celebrate the richness of life without fear of a psychotic despot in the sky who would kill me for not belonging to some obscure group. I am currently interested in learning about Unitarian Universalism, but Agnostic Atheist would best describe my views about dieties and the supernatural. I am also a Secular Humanist, as I believe in aiding my fellow humans to lead rich, healthy lives.After working as a snowcone salesman, I learned I love pleasing others. I am studying to become a nurse and I am in the process of becoming licensed as a pharmacy tech.--Here's an update after 8 more years of aging and growing in the world. I'm still living in Louisiana, and the nursing and pharmacy tech careers weren't for me. I've grown surly and more introverted, and I now work as a high school special education teacher. I look at the world with more jaundiced eyes and prefer the safety and security of my current work to any kind of chaos. I learned with age that "adventuring" usually doesn't turn out so well. It has fallen to ash......And the butterflies in my stomach are starving.They'd much better be moths drawn to the blaze...Tell me-- is this how the fleeting saturniidae are born?"                                           -(modified) poem by meHello, there. The name's Dea (Day-uh), if you don't feel like constantly pronouncing the scientific name of a moth family.  Feel free to chat if you'd like. I promise, I'm friendly.
